  <span id="freeText710871450057571195" style="display:none">Five stars. This book is beautiful. It took me months and months to get through; this is no easy to read “how-to” manual on marriage, but rather a deeply spiritual discussion of oneness and mutual submission. Where better than marriage to practice our faith and reflect the gospel - the laying down of our will for the sake of another, choosing to use whatever gift we’ve been given to serve others, loving when it is not earned. Especially then! “Too often others are but the punctuation marks in the dry and windy monologues of our own self-centered existence.” —- I am encouraged that the mystery and magic of marriage can cure this self-centeredness in me if I will allow it to do its work. And the work is done by true love, and the mystery by two becoming one; what a gift. </span>
