        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1811261697" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2394125479412749743">This is like no other book on marriage that I&apos;ve ever seen. It&apos;s certainly not your typical &quot;how to&quot; study on having a good Christian marriage. Mike Mason delves deeply in to the theology of Christian marriage; the mystery behind it that makes it humbling and fulfilling, wonderful and disturbing, awesome and mundane all at once. Mason&apos;s word craft is superb. His writing is almost poetic, richly describing the mystery and the miracle of marriage. Well worth reading together with one&apos;s spouse and </span>
  <span id="freeText2394125479412749743" style="display:none">This is like no other book on marriage that I've ever seen. It's certainly not your typical "how to" study on having a good Christian marriage. Mike Mason delves deeply in to the theology of Christian marriage; the mystery behind it that makes it humbling and fulfilling, wonderful and disturbing, awesome and mundane all at once. Mason's word craft is superb. His writing is almost poetic, richly describing the mystery and the miracle of marriage. Well worth reading together with one's spouse and pondering the wondrous thoughts that this book evokes.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2394125479412749743" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

