  <span id="freeText11006474750166787456" style="display:none">First book finished in the new year! Woohoo!<br /><br />This was a wonderful meditation to start 2019 off with. My grandmother recommended it to me at my wedding shower and now, three years in, I finally got around to it. <br /><br />This was so refreshingly different from any marriage book that we've read together. It's less a, "how to have an awesome marriage" and more of a, "this is what is at the heart of marriage and how it points to God." Really breathtaking and all around fascinating to read. <br /><br />He is quite wordy though and lost me more than once with his lofty ideas and language. Not a light read by any means.</span>
