        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4265541711" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11523966857304488422">Still trying to decide what I think about this. Some absolute gems and really beautiful reflections on marriage. The format (it really is a collection of short meditations) makes it easy to pick up, read just a page or two, and put down. <br/><br/>It felt overly flowery and idealistic at times, and more than once I had the thought that someone in a difficult or painful marriage would find it more demoralizing than encouraging. <br/><br/>On the whole I think I&apos;d recommend, but with the caveats that 1-you won&apos;t have </span>
  <span id="freeText11523966857304488422" style="display:none">Still trying to decide what I think about this. Some absolute gems and really beautiful reflections on marriage. The format (it really is a collection of short meditations) makes it easy to pick up, read just a page or two, and put down. <br /><br />It felt overly flowery and idealistic at times, and more than once I had the thought that someone in a difficult or painful marriage would find it more demoralizing than encouraging. <br /><br />On the whole I think I'd recommend, but with the caveats that 1-you won't have much patience for it if you don't prefer poetic ruminations, and 2-you will be much more likely to enjoy it if your marriage is healthy, satisfying and thriving. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11523966857304488422" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


